quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  44,1,"Ha'. Mim."
  44,2,"By the Clear Book."
  44,3,"We revealed it on a Blessed Night, for We were intent on warning;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  44,4,"(We revealed it on the Night) wherein every matter is wisely determined"{1},footnotes:1:1
  44,5,"by Our command. Verily, We were set to send a Messenger"{1},footnotes:1:1
  44,6,"as a Mercy from your Lord. Surely He is All-Hearing, All-Seeing,"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  44,7,"the Lord of the heavens and the earth and of all that is between them: if you would only have sure faith."{1},footnotes:1:1
  44,8,"There is no god but He: He gives life and causes death. He is your Lord and the Lord of your forefathers of yore."{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  44,9,"(But the fact is, they lack certainty) and frolic about in doubt."{1},footnotes:1:1
  44,10,"So watch for the Day when the sky will come down with a pall of smoke,"